 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/utwiggietymberwolf.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Twiggie Tymberwolf</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Protector of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 273<br> <font color=#CC9900>(1/14/01 12:16:42 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Fear Question</span><hr size=1> Few things I can answer since I'm not an expert but will try to help with these.<br>
<br>
I know of 3 golems.  Fright, Terror, and Dread. One of the maps at Eqmaps shows the location of each I believe.<br>
<br>
The bone dragon was Dracoliche (sp?).  7 day spawn time. <br>
<br>
The Temple is the castle shown on the map.  Its in the middle of the fire ring.   The portal out of Fear is located in the temple.   Alot of Amy's are in the temple.  <br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#414141><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uminutemanaslayer.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Minute Manaslayer</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Adventurer of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 117<br> <font color=#CC9900>(1/15/01 10:26:32 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Fear Question</span><hr size=1> The puller kept saying that the first person that attacked the golem was going to get death touched.  So I'm assuming that as soon as a golem is attacked CT comes running? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uaraden.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Araden</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Protector of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 358<br> <font color=#CC9900>(1/16/01 1:02:22 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Fear Question</span><hr size=1> aye, CT starts DTing soon as a golem gets actually hit.  the way you do the golems is pound it and then everyone camps to wipe agro.  rinse n repeat for the remaining two golems..<br>
<br>
Kalandril Wyndrider, druid 52<br>
Araden Aerosmithe, ranger 46<br>
Kenek, monk 39<br>
<br>
P.S.  Thanks for havin me DG, learned a lot.  can't wait to try out amy temple pulls like Kruunch there did em, should help CA out a lot doing it that way, seemed to make things a lot easier than the way we'd been doing it <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#414141><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ubarrinsoulburner.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Barrin Soulburner</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>some newbie</span><br>  Posts: 308<br> <font color=#CC9900>(1/16/01 3:39:41 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://eq.geauxonline.com/watchers/barrin.jpg h=496 w=293></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Fear Question</span><hr size=1> Actually if you want you don't have to kill the golems till the very end.  They are just annoying in the fact that if you kill them before CT is down you have to camp after each one.  Much easier to leave them up and mez them after they come to aid CT (when you attack him). <p><a href=http://www.eqforge.com/profiles/profile.cfm?ID=5173>Barrin Soulburner</a><br>
Watchers</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/udyninvifargent.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Dynin Vifargent</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Protector of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 1112<br> <font color=#CC9900>(1/16/01 10:55:45 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Fear Question</span><hr size=1> 1) only 1-2 mobs roam there every once in a while, so when you fight there you will not get unwanted agro<br>
the advantage of pulling along the wall is that you have less chances to have mobs roam and end up behind you when you are pulling, it's also an easy way to CT as it allows you to clear the zone around him<br>
<br>
2) pretty much only roamers everywhere in the zone<br>
there is a gorgon nest, a scare tower, a fetid fiend house and a frightfinger house though<br>
one of the best maps to see where the specific locations are :<br>
<!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://www.everlore.com/geography/default.asp?mapID=14380">www.everlore.com/geograph...apID=14380</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--><br>
<br>
3) the 3 golems are in small temples on the top of 3 hills, and have 2 amy guards each<br>
there are also roaming amys, plus a shit load of them in the temple (in the fire circle)<br>
<br>
4) Dracoliche<br>
cazic's personal bodyguard<br>
he roams pretty much everywhere in the zone and is a pain in the ass because it makes you pull around him (it doesnt matter as much on high level raids though since people can kill him petty much any time)<br>
very hard to control when you pull him<br>
<br>
5) the temple is inside the fire ring<br>
there is a bunch of amys and a few phobos as well<br>
pulling the temple has always been a blast and one of the only thing i still enjoy in the game (kiting 10 amys around will never get old)<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
the stagin points in fear are pretty much the same all the time and tend to be the same on all the servers, because they are easy to spot<br>
<br>
some people like more to mass enter the zone and break it from the portal, but i would only do it with experienced people<br>
<br>
due to the pathing, clearing the plane like this is the easiest and most effective way to do it imo<br>
<br>
pulling the temple without agroing CT can be tricky, but it's just a problem of timing.. just need to get used to it <p><BR>
 <B>Dynin Vifargent</B></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#414141><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ukruuunch.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kruuunch</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_fire.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Ugliest Paladin o' Kaladim</span><br>  Posts: 1219<br> <font color=#CC9900>(1/16/01 12:55:49 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.krunch.net/kruunch-face.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Fear Question</span><hr size=1> 3 ways I've seen Fear done.<br>
<br>
Main Kiter/assistant puller.<br>
<br>
Pull group mez/mem blur extras on pulls.<br>
<br>
Monk FD pulling with chainer.<br>
<br>
The first one is the one we used to break the speed record and works the best IMHO.<br>
<br>
Monk/chaining is probably the easiest and safest. That and you can pull Gorgons through the GY if you are planning on doing a short stint in Fear.<br>
<br>
Temple pulls are messy and except for a flawless pull, will take you upwards of an hour or more to complete. Even with a flawless pull and godo team, it will take you 30 mins.<br>
<br>
It's a cardinal sin to leave CT up these days. <p><FONT face="arial" size="-1"><B>Kruunch Spiritslammer (Ugliest Paladin o' Kaladim)
